<p><b>Background:</b><br>
I joined UMass after receiving my PhD
from
Carnegie Mellon University's
<a href=http://www.ml.cmu.edu/>Machine Learning Department</a>.
I have also been a 
Visiting Fellow at <a href=http://www.iq.harvard.edu/>Harvard IQSS</a>,
and
interned with the <a href=https://research.fb.com/category/data-science/>Facebook Data Science</a> team.
Before grad school,
I worked on crowdsourced annotations at CrowdFlower / Dolores Labs,
and
natural language search at Powerset.

I started studying the intersection of AI and social science
as an undergrad/masters student in 
Stanford
<a href=http://symsys.stanford.edu>Symbolic Systems</a> (cognitive science, more or less).

